<center><b><FONT Size=2 Face=Tahoma,Arial COLOR=#3232CD>Dalharen d'Oloth ~ The Seventh Hammer</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umikar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/13/01 7:16:49 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Form vs. function</span><hr size=1> Its not *just* about taunt or *just* about ratio.<br>
<br>
Prior to level 20 the Wurmslayer is a bad weapon because you are capped in how hard you can hit.<br>
<br>
At level 20 and forward for quite some levels the Wurmslayer is an incredible weapon. Its ratio means it far outdamages any other (realistic) weapon and the extra damage will be a large enough taunt to offset the less taunt coming from fewer swings.<br>
<br>
As you approach level 40 the damage from weapons like a Jade Mace will get closer to that of the Wurmslayer to surpass it at level ~43 due to the fact that you get a damage bonus per swing in the main hand as you level - so its not just about the ratio of the weapon. Further, the lack of taunt value due to fewer swings might start to hurt.<br>
<br>
So, from level 20 to level 35-43 the Wurmslayer is a splendid weapon *IF* you have 100 sta or more because then being oos only means you cannot jump but doesnt otherwise effect your performance. But then, which warrior doesnt have 100 sta.<br>
<br>
